      "content": "Wait, \"proprietary economic forecasts\"? We don't actually have any new proprietary forecasts. If the reporter asks to see the source of these \"cutting-edge\" models to verify the change, we're going to look like we're making it up on the fly. That's a huge risk. Wouldn't it be safer to just say the candidate's perspective has matured on the issue rather than inventing a specific source of data we don't possess?",
